node.text: Join me in my #2Days200Dollars challenge by choosing any space in your home to makeover in 2 days with just 200 dollars!  This is a fun challenge meant to inspire you to take action and create a space you love without taking tons of time or money.  Let's get started 👊😘 Be sure to share what you're doing by tagging me @cynthia_harper_ and I'll choose some of my favorite transformations to share in my stories/posts/blog! 🙌

node.text: The stairs are DONE 🎉  But here's a moment of raw honesty:  What you see is a smiling face and beautiful new stairwell.  And normal Instagram protocol would make this a celebratory post of a project completed.  Don't get me wrong, I am truly proud of how this budget friendly makeover turned out.  But I almost feel fake putting this smiling image up when I'm struggling through some hard things in real life.  So this post is dedicated to putting one foot in front of the other.  To showing up and creating beauty & joy when it's lacking.  To continuing to work hard to make things better...in my home...and in my life.  Thanks for all the love, support, and kindness you've shown throughout this project.  You guys have been more of a lifeline than you know ❤  xo, Cynthia

node.text: Part 1 of the stairs is DONE 👏🎉   I could swipe back and forth between this Before & After all day long.  It's crazy what a difference some paint and a good runner can make!  This project wasn't originally on my list but I needed a simple project to be my therapy right now.  And working creatively with my hands definitely lifts my spirits a bit.  This view from the top of the stairs might make things look finished, but there's still a bottom section of stairs to complete and the railings to DIY.  I'm grateful to keep working on this.  It's gonna be good!

node.text: Her in those sunglasses is such a vibe 🍍✌ And it pretty much sums up my level of excitement about @amazon Prime Day coming up on June 21 & 22! #Ad  I admire that Amazon has made it easy to support small businesses on #PrimeDay while still enjoying that fast, free delivery we all know and love.  One of my fave small businesses is @beeswrap which is owned by a mom of 3 that creates reusable food wraps from beeswax to help reduce single-use plastic waste and live more sustainably.  Have you heard of beeswax food wraps?  I was initially a little skeptical of how they'd work but they're durable, can be washed with soap and water, and reused for up to a year (head to my stories for a tutorial).  This year, Prime members who spend $10 on select small business products from June 7-20, get a $10 credit to spend on #PrimeDay. Head to amazon.com/supportsmall to learn more! #PrimeLife

node.text: A peep of my stair runner progress, aka: today's therapy session 🙌  I decided to stray from my all-neutral tendencies, and try a little color instead.  And I love it!!!   These colors, this fun pattern...it makes me feel happy.  I've got a lot of stairs left to finish, but I'm grateful for this project as a much-needed creative outlet right now.  I know I already said this in stories, but thank you for all your supportive & kind DMs last night. You guys are the best community of people, and you mean more to me than you know ❤  xo, Cynthia

node.text: From a blank porch wall...to a hanging herb garden 🌱  I really wanted a large garden this year, but I honestly just don't have the energy.  So instead I decided to create a hanging herb garden on this existing porch wall.  #ad I figured if it's front & center on my porch, I can't forget to water it regularly (which is usually my problem, lol😂).  I created cute little labels from paint stir sticks and my @officialcricut machine, and added them to these planters.  Then I screwed them onto my existing porch wall, and now I've got my very own cute & practical herb garden that I can tend to & nurture all summer long! 👊  #cricutmade

node.text: See that "new" trunk?👀👆 When I was a kid, we'd go thrift store shopping, mostly out of necessity because it was what we could afford.  I always loved the thrill of the hunt and getting a good deal!!  But I'd never tell my friends that I thrift store shopped because I was embarrassed what they might think.  So I kept it to myself and silently hoped I'd never run into anyone I knew while thrifting🙈  Fast forward 2 decades, and now I excitedly share my thrifting hauls with thousands of YOU.  I love that you are my people. That you "get" me.  And I love that I've grown more comfortable in my own skin as I've gotten older.  Last week Bean found that trunk at a thrift store and with a simple whitewash mix of water & paint we gave it a subdued finish that helped it fit into our home better.  I love thrifted finds.   I love simple projects with my daughter.  And I love doing life with each of you!  Thanks for hanging out with me here each day. It means more than me than you know 💛 xo, Cynthia

node.text: My jeans are tight. And I was in a funk all morning  because of it.  But then I reminded myself of something:  these legs have carried and birthed babies, have walked alongside friends during times of immense loss, have climbed the Austrian Alps, wandered the Puerto Rican rainforest, loved my husband, built a thriving business out of thin air, and taken meals to people in need.   They've carried me through the highest of highs and the lowest of lows, and they keep putting one foot in front of the other every single day, which is a gift in itself.  I'd say these legs have served me pretty darn well over the years. So why in the world am I upset because they won't squeeze into a certain size anymore?  What if we spent more time appreciating our bodies for what they can DO rather than how they appear?!   I'm giving myself permission to age...to expand.  To be happy with the beautiful life I'm living, rather than allow my emotions to be controlled by a number on a tag.  I've only got one life to live and I'd rather spend it embracing a softer and happier me, than strive for some "ideal" version of myself that makes me personally miserable along the way.  Just sharing my thoughts, in case anyone else needed to hear them today 💛👖 xo, Cynthia

node.text: I'll be the first to admit, I do not cook a meal every night.  I learned long ago to let go of the mom-guilt associated with that, and am perfectly content on busy nights to do what my kids call "snackie" dinner 🙌  I'll grab a platter and toss on some crackers,  @RothCheese, salami, veggies and fruit for us to eat. The kids think they're having snacks for dinner (that's how it got the name "snackie" dinner years ago!) so they're happy. And Chris loves anything involving cheese, so he's always down for snackie dinner too.  We've been enjoying the new creamy Spinach Artichoke Gouda by @RothCheese - it's so creamy & definitely takes a cheeseboard to the next level!  And it's easy to find because it's available on @AmazonFresh so I can order it right to my doorstep.   Honestly these kinds of dinners are some of my favorite because there's no exhaustion or chaos from cooking a full meal and I can truly just enjoy my cute company and the conversation 💛  #rothpartner #spinachartichokegouda #rothcheese

node.text: Would you believe these modern planters are made from old tomatoes cages that I plucked out of overgrown weeds?! 🌱🍅 Yup, true story.   All it took was a can of spraypaint, 2 new white pots from Target (total of $11), and a little creativity.  And, Boom.  Modern planters for a fraction of the cost of store-bought ones, while repurposing something I already owned 👊  I'm always fascinated by finding new ways to use the most ordinary items!!  And these tomato cages were no exception.  I realize these aren't heirloom quality planters but I love the look of them, and how they can easily transition to be indoors or outdoors. You can see the simple behind-the-scenes process in my stories. And be sure to check in with my fellow DIY garden buddies @_forthehome @thesassybarn & @joineryanddesignco to see the creative ideas they shared in their stories today!

node.text: The door is done!  👏👏   DONE!  This project tested my patience. Made quite a few of you mad when I removed the ornate detail piece 🙈  And left me wanting to quit a few times because the process was so messy and hard. (Swipe to see the 'Before' pic.)  BUT I'm glad I stuck with it, because sitting here now I can say it was worth it after all!  It adds so much character to this space, and let's natural LIGHT into our windowless galley-style laundry room, which was our original intention all along ☀️  Sometimes the journey is hard, but the end result makes it all worth it.

node.text: From an empty soap dispenser headed to the trash 👉 to a beautiful antique-looking amber bud vase at no cost!!   All it took was a little dirt, glue, and creativity!  The real test will be when you see it up close, so swipe to how it turned out.  The one on the left in the second photo is the authentic antique amber bottle and the one on the right is the new soap dispenser with my DIY dirt makeover.  What do you think?!  Not too bad for a no cost project that also kept an item out of the landfill 🙌    Head to stories to see the before picture and the behind-the-scenes process (it's really simple and even kid-friendly too!) I hope this inspires you to look at items in a new light and get creative with repurposing what you already have! 💛  xo, Cynthia
